Ask HN: How text AI generators aren't the end of search engines?
text:
CMV: it's over for search engines. The quality was already on the decline. now with text generated actually MORE coherent and more readable, how can search engine figure this out on a scale.

I predict forums/QA/chats are going to become more dominant moving forward.

Ask HN: What is your opinion on Fake Door Testing?
text:
What do you think about Fake Door Testing? Is is a valid strategy to quickly validate ideas or do you find it dishonest?

For those who don't know what it is, here is an example scenario: You want to implement a new feature, but even the MVP will take +3 months to implement. So instead, you make a minimum UI without any business logic and when the users click on the button you tell them "coming soon" and then you test how many people wanted to interact with the feature and if it is worth it.
